SIMPLE: scantly
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scantly
<hw>Scant"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a scant manner;
not fully or sufficiently; narrowly; penuriously.</def>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Scarcely; hardly; barely.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Scantly</qex> they durst their feeble eyes dispread⟦br⟧
Upon that town.</q> <rj><qau>Fairfax.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We hold a tourney here to-morrow morn,⟦br⟧
And there is <qex>scantly</qex> time for half the work.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scantness</ent>⟦br⟧
